# Documentation Rules

## Voice & Tense
- Active voice, present tense, second person ("you")
- No: "simply", "just", "easy", "obviously"

## Structure
- Lead with what the user can DO
- Overview → Details → Reference

## Code Examples
- Must be runnable and tested
- Realistic names, not foo/bar
- Comments only for non-obvious lines

## Headings
- Sentence case
- H2 → H3 max depth
